AGI - Arrest on the night at the university campus of George Washington University > in Washington DC, where police cleared the occupied area > from April 25 by pro-Palestina protesters. According to the police, an imprecise number of people occupying the university was not formed by students but by outsiders. The agents also used pepper spray > to remove the protesters. Operations began at 3 o'clock at night: Many occupants were sleeping, others were studying to prepare the final exams of the academic year. The school leaders recalled "that freedom of expression must be defended but the camp has led to illegal actions and in violation of university regulations".
&nbsp;
In recent days, a flag of Palestine had been exposed on the roof of one of the campus buildings. The flag was removed. The police blitz arrived a week after visiting the university by six representatives of the House Supervisory Board and later, explained the Washington Police Department, that "the situation had recorded an escalation of the protest". Currently there are 140 universities and colleges in the United States occupied by demonstrations of solidarity with the Palestinians.

